"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":15,"id":"fb3d0913","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-11T16:46:46.18022Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-11T16:46:46.180117Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-11T16:46:46.385522Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-11T16:46:46.385274Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.211017,"end_time":"2026-04-11T16:46:46.386023+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-11T16:46:46.175006+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["\n"," LoRA adapter saved to: /kaggle/working/nemotron_lora_adapter\n","   Adapter size: 44.1 MB\n","   Disk remaining: 19.4 GB\n"]}],"source":["ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH = \"/kaggle/working/nemotron_lora_adapter\"\n","model.save_pretrained(ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH, safe_serialization=True)\n","tokenizer.save_pretrained(ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH)\n","\n","# Report disk usage\n","import shutil\n","adapter_size = sum(\n","    os.path.getsize(os.path.join(dp, f))\n","    for dp, _, fns in os.walk(ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH)\n","    for f in fns\n",") / (1024 * 1024)\n","disk_usage = shutil.disk_usage(\"/kaggle/working\")\n","print(f\"\\n LoRA adapter saved to: {ADAPTER_SAVE_PATH}\")\n","print(f\"   Adapter size: {adapter_size:.1f} MB\")\n","print(f\"   Disk remaining: {disk_usage.free / (1024**3):.1f} GB\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"21f2eda4","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.004619,"end_time":"2026-04-11T16:46:46.395351+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-11T16:46:46.390732+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## Step 9: Inference Test\n","\n","A quick inference test is run to verify the model has learned the required output format. A math problem is passed to the model with the reasoning system prompt active. The generated output is checked for:\n","\n","- A closing `</think>` tag -- confirms the model learned to close its chain-of-thought block.\n","- A `\\\\boxed{}` final answer -- confirms the model learned to produce a structured answer.\n","